study_description: A collection of de novo variants in children diagnosed with 6 developmental disorders (autism, schizophrenia, intellectual disability, developmental disorder, epilepsy, congenital heart disease), and in typically developing children. This dataset includes: - **SD_autism** A collection of de novo variants identified in collections of families with autism. - **SD_autism_ssc** A collection of de novo variants identified in the Simons Simplex Collection. - **SD_EichlerTG2012_liftover** Targeted resequencing of 44 genes in 2446 ASD probands reported in O'Roak et al., *Science*, 2012. - **SD_EichlerWE2012_liftover** Whole exome sequencing of 667 individual exomes from 209 simplex families reported in O’Roak, B. et al., *Nature* 2012. - **SD_IossifovWE2014_liftover** Whole exome sequencing of more than 2,500 simplex families, each having a child with an autistic spectrum disorder reported in Iossifov, I. et al., *Nature*, 2014.. - **SD_Krumm2015_SNVindel_liftover** A set of exonic single-nucleotide variants (SNVs) from 2,377 families with autism reported in Krumm, N. et al., *Nat Genet*, 2015. - **SD_ORoakTG2014_SSC_liftover** Resequencing of 64 candidate neurodevelopmental disorder risk genes in 5,979 individuals - 3,486 probands and 2,493 unaffected siblings reported in O'Roak, B. et al., *Nat Commun*, 2014. - **SD_SFARI_SSC_WGS_CSHL_DENOVO** Whole genome sequence (WGS) of simplex families from the Simons Simplex Collection (SSC) reported in Yoon, S. et al., *Commun Biol*, 2021. - **SD_Turner2017_liftover** Genome sequence data from 516 idiopathic autism families (2,064 individuals) reported in Turner T. et al., *Cell*, 2017. - **SD_Werling2018_liftover** Whole genome sequencing data from 519 autism spectrum disorder families reported in Werling, D.M. et al., *Nat Genet*, 2018. - **SD_autism_spark** A collection of de novo variants identified in the SPARK Collection. - **SD_iWES_v1_1_genotypes_DENOVO** Whole-exome sequencing of saliva DNA from more than 30,000 SPARK families. - **SD_autism_other** A collection of de novo variants identified in various collections of families with ASD. - **SD_ACS2014_liftover** Whole exome sequencing of 3,871 autism cases and 9,937 ancestry-matched or parental controls reported in De Rubeis S. et al., *Nature*, 2014. - **SD_AGRE_WG38_859_DENOVO** Whole genome sequence (WGS) of multiplex families from the Autism Genetic Resource Exchange (AGRE) reported in Yoon, S. et al., *Commun Biol*, 2021. - **SD_ORoakTG2014_TASC_liftover** Resequencing of 64 candidate neurodevelopmental disorder risk genes in 5,979 individuals - 3,486 probands and 2,493 unaffected siblings reported in O'Roak, B. et al., *Nat Commun*, 2014.. - **SD_Yuen2017_liftover** Whole genome sequencing of 5,205 samples from families with ASD reported in C Yuen R., et al., *Nat Neurosci*, 2017. - **SD_Takata2018_liftover** Whole exome sequencing of 262 ASD probands of Japanese origin reported in Takata A. et al., *Cell Reports*, 2018. - **SD_congenital_heart_disease** A collection of de novo variants identified in families with congenital heart disease (CHD). - **SD_Chung2015CHD_liftover** Exome sequencing of 1213 CHD parent-offspring trios reported in Homsy, J. et al., *Science*, 2015. - **SD_developmental_disorder** A collection of de novo variants identified in families containing individuals with developmental disorders. - **SD_DDD2017_liftover** Whole exome sequencing of 4,293 families containing individuals with developmental disorders reported in Deciphering Developmental Disorders Study, *Nature*, 2017. - **SD_epilepsy** A collection of de novo variants identified in individuals with epilepsy. - **SD_Epi4KWE2013_liftover** Whole exome sequencing of 264 probands and their parents reported in Epi4K Consortium., *Nature*, 2013. - **SD_Helbig2016_liftover** Exome sequencing of 1,131 patients with epilepsy reported in Helbid K. et al., *Genet Med*, 2016. - **SD_intellectual_disability** A collection of de novo variants identified in individuals with intellectual disability. - **SD_Lelieveld2016_liftover** Exome sequencing of 2,104 patient-parent trios with intellectual disability reported in Lelieveld, S. et al., *Nat Neurosci*, 2016. - **SD_VissersWE2012_liftover** Exome sequencing of 100 patients with an IQ below 50 and their unaffected parents reported in de Ligt, J. et al., *N Engl J Med*, 2012. - **SD_Rauch2012_liftover** Exome sequencing of 51 children with intellectual disability and their parents and 20 controls reported in Rauch a. et al., *Lancet*, 2012. - **SD_schizophrenia** A collection of de novo variants identified in individuals with schizophrenia. - **SD_GulsunerSchWE2013_liftover** Exome sequencing of 105 probands, 84 unaffected siblings, and their 210 unaffected parents reported in S. Gulsuner et al., *Cell*, 2013. - **SD_KarayiorgouWE2012_liftover** Exome sequencing of 231 parent-proband trios with schizophrenia and 34 unaffected trios reported in Xu, B. et al., *Nat Genet*, 2012. - **SD_ODonovanWE2014_liftover** Exome sequencing of 623 parent-proband trios, where the proband had a history of hospitalization for schizophrenia or schizoaffective disorder reported in Fromer, M. et al., *Nature*, 2014. - **SD_McCarthy2014_liftover** Exome sequencing of 57 trios with sporadic or familial schizophrenia reported in McCarthy, S. et al., *Mol Psychiatry*, 2014.
